<br>
1. All drops are NBG unless otherwise stated.<br>
2. Last Piece Rule will always be in effect.<br>
3. Defaulted to someone (which will be announced at the beginning of each raid)<br>
4. Epic pieces will go to whomever the epic raid is for.<br>
<br>
The other side of the Loot system regarding Colossus, <br>
Weighted Rolls.  The best way to describe weighted rolls and how they apply to Colossus is as follows:<br>
<br>
1.  Raids are desigated as 51% of the guild in a raid window, in the same zone, at the same camp.  <br>
2.  Every raid attendee will receive One(1) point towards their Weighted Roll(WR) pool.  <br>
3.  WR points are then spent to give yourself an extra &quot;number&quot; towards a roll regarding a piece of loot.<br>
4.  WR points are NOT subtracted from your pool if you do NOT win.  <br>
5.  If you do win, all points spent on the roll will be subtracted from your overall points.  <br>
<br>
An example of the WR system in place:<br>
<br>
  A Corroded BP drops in Kael.  WarriorA, WarriorB, PaladinC, and ShadowknightD would like to roll.  WarriorA spends 4 WR point and receives 5 Numbers(his 1 default roll and 4 WR points) on the /random roll.  So, the random roll would look like this: WarriorA 1-5, WarriorB 6, PaladinC 7, ShadowknightD 8.  The roll would then commence and WarriorA would have a severe advantage over the other participants.  <br>
<br>
Any non-guild members who attend a raid will still receive their default number just like a normal NBG roll, although guild members will still be able to use their points towards that roll.<br>
<br>
This loot system is not final and can be changed at anytime should the majority(51%) of the guild deem it unworthy or flawed.  <br>
<br>
This is in essence how the loot system in our guild works.  Chris and Kristell will keep track of everyone's WR points.  WR points will NOT be assigned until the END of every raid.  So you will not receive WR points for the current evening of raiding until the next day.  <br>
<br>
